http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Sawang-to-be-chief-guest-at-The-Hindu-quiz-contest/article14006879.ece

The 16th anniversary of The Hindu Young World Quiz , one of the longest-running and largest live school quizzes, will be organised in Vijayawada on January 20. The quiz will be hosted by The Hindu ’s resident quizmaster V.V. Ramanan. Vijayawada Police Commissioner Gautham Sawang, the chief guest at the programme, will give away prizes to the winners.The contest will have two categories: Juniors (Classes IV to VI) and Seniors (Classes VII to IX). Junior quiz competitions will be held in Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Vijayawada and Visakhapatnam, while competitions for seniors will be held in Bengaluru, Mangaluru, Hubballi, Hyderabad, Vijayawada and Visakhapatnam.The competition in Vijayawada will be conducted on January 20 at Siddhartha Academy Auditorium.Spot registrations will be held for students in the junior category from 9 a.m. onwards. The quiz programme will begin at 10 a.m. Similarly, the spot registrations for students in the senior category will begin at 1 p.m., and the quiz will begin at 2 p.m. For those who want to register online, the last date has been extended by a day and they can register on Tuesday also.The 16th edition of the quiz is being presented (sponsored) by the Vellore Institute of Technology (VIT) and powered by the State Bank of India (SBI).Firefox is the national gift partner and Kokuyo Camlin is the goodie partner. Vijayawada edition head V.V. Raja Rao (mobile number – +919849211799) can be contacted for information and www.thehindu.com/vwquiz is the online link.Those not able to register online can register on the spot at the venue an hour before the quiz contest as per the timing mentioned above.